The ALR code, written on R, does not require installation, but it has dependencies that must be satisfied:

- R (in Ubuntu: apt install r-base)
- R.utils (in Ubuntu: apt install r-cran-r.utils)
- MatrixStats (in Ubuntu: apt install r-cran-matrixstats)
    
To run ALR from Python, the following dependencies have to be satisfied:

- Python 3 (in Ubuntu: apt install python3)
- numpy (e.g., pip3 install numpy)
- rpy2 (e.g., pip3 install rpy2)
- matplotlib (e.g., pip3 install matplotlib)
